Package polyglot.frontend

Class Compiler

java.lang.Object
polyglot.frontend.Compiler
public class Compiler
extends java.lang.Object
This is the main entry point for the compiler. It contains a work list that contains entries for all classes that must be compiled (or otherwise worked on).

    • compileFiles

      public boolean compileFiles​(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> filenames)
      Compile all the files listed in the set of strings source. Return true on success. The method outputFiles can be used to obtain the output of the compilation. This is the main entry point for the compiler, called from main().

    • compile

      public boolean compile​(java.util.Collection<FileSource> sources)
      Compile all the files listed in the set of Sources source. Return true on success. The method outputFiles can be used to obtain the output of the compilation. This is the main entry point for the compiler, called from main().
